<%# locals: (user:, summary: nil) -%>
<%# Visually-hidden span referenced by the bell link's `aria-labelledby`
    (D1). Lives in its own broadcast frame (`notifications_bell_label_frame`)
    so the bell link stays stable across notification arrivals — replacing
    the label leaves the focusable link intact, so clicks landing during a
    broadcast still hit a live element. Mirrors the existing
    `_notifications_bell` pattern (separate frame for the visual indicator)
    so each surface updates independently.

    Accepts an optional pre-computed `summary:` local so a parent partial
    (e.g. `_notifications_bell_link`) can share ONE
    `unread_notification_breakdown` query across the bell label and the
    severity indicator. Falls back to its own query when rendered
    standalone (e.g. via Turbo Stream broadcast). -%>
<% summary ||= unread_notification_summary(user) %>
<span id="notifications_bell_label" class="sr-only">
  <%= bell_link_aria_label(user, summary) %>
</span>
